econet-eth: account BQL before ringing QDMA TX doorbell

The TX completion path calls netdev_tx_completed_queue(), which ends in
dql_completed().  That code BUG_ONs if the driver completes more bytes than
were queued.

en75_dev_xmit() posted the descriptor and rang the QDMA doorbell inside
en75_qdma_xmit(), then only afterwards called netdev_tx_sent_queue().  On this
SoC small packets can complete very quickly, and the threaded TX done NAPI can
run before en75_dev_xmit() reaches the enqueue-side BQL accounting.  The result
is a legitimate completion racing ahead of the accounting and tripping:

  dql_completed: BUG_ON(count > num_queued - dql->num_completed)

Keep the accounting tied to the descriptor itself and perform the enqueue-side
BQL update immediately before the QDMA doorbell.  Completion then uses the
stored netdev_queue/length rather than skb->dev at completion time; that also
keeps direct internal QDMA users, such as the WHNAT probe, out of BQL unless
the normal netdev xmit path explicitly supplied a TX queue.

Also stop the selected netdev queue before the doorbell when this descriptor
consumes the last free slot.  That closes the companion stop/wake race where a
very fast completion could wake queues before en75_dev_xmit() got around to
stopping the just-filled queue.

